!! Important: Notice the different methods shown above for accessing an element of a pointer (a) versus an element of a reference (c) The following example shows the Dot struct containing the RGB struct as an element. If you apply syn.directive.disaggregate to variable Arr, then only the top-level Dot struct is disa...
struct Pixel {
    char R;
    char G;
    char B;
};
struct Dot {
    Pixel RGB;
    unsigned Size;
};
#define N 1086
void DUT(Dot Arr[N]) {
...
}
syn. directive. disaggregate=DUT Arr

