By default:
By default, the following code results in a single RTL implementation of function func\_sub for all three instances, or if func\_sub is a small function it is inlined into function func. ★ Tip: By default, the Vitis HLS tool automatically inlines small functions. This is true even for function instantiations. Using...
char func_sub(char inval, char incr)
{
    return inval + incr;
}

void func(char inval1, char inval2, char inval3,
    char *outval1, char *outval2, char *outval3)
{
    *outval1 = func_sub(inval1, 1);
    *outval2 = func_sub(inval2, 2);
    *outval3 = func_sub(inval3, 3);
}

